SIMPLE: deferent
RECORDS: 2

==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Deferent
<hw>Def"er*ent</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>a.</pos> <ety>[L.
<ets>deferens</ets>, p. pr. of <ets>deferre</ets>. See 3d
<er>Defer</er>.]</ety> <def>Serving to carry; bearing.</def>
<mark>[R.]</mark> ⟦ldquo⟧Bodies <xex>deferent</xex>.⟦rdquo⟧
<rj><au>Bacon.</au></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Deferent</ent>⟦br⟧

==== ENTRY 2 ====
HEADWORD: Deferent
<hw>Def"er*ent</hw>, <pos>n.</pos> <sn>1.</sn> <def>That which carries
or conveys.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><q>Though air be the most favorable <qex>deferent</qex> of
sounds.</q> <rj><qau>Bacon.</qau></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>2.</sn> <fld>(Ptolemaic Astron.)</fld> <def>An imaginary circle
surrounding the earth, in whose periphery either the heavenly body or
the center of the heavenly body's epicycle was supposed to be carried
round.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Deferential</ent>⟦br⟧
